# Linux for Cybersecurity

This section covers the Linux training completed as part of my
Cybersecurity Professional Certification.

## Topics Covered
- Linux file system and directory structure
- File and directory permissions
- Users and groups management
- Process management
- Package management (apt, yum)
- Networking commands
- Bash basics
- Log analysis

## Key Commands Practiced
- ls, cd, pwd, tree
- chmod, chown, umask
- ps, top, htop, kill
- grep, awk, sed
- netstat, ss, ip, ping
- journalctl, dmesg

## Tools & Environments
- Ubuntu / Kali Linux
- Bash Shell
- SSH

## Use Cases in Cybersecurity
- Log monitoring and analysis
- System hardening
- Incident response
- Network troubleshooting
